  "body": "\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-97c4f63dff1f0105691bc55566c438a3 wp-block-paragraph\">Guide to using the Team Schedule module to view a company-wide Gantt of all staff project assignments, and how to log and review timesheet entries for individual team members.</p>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-53093\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"448\" src=\"/images/recon/Add-a-heading-41-1024x448.webp\" width=\"1024\"/></figure>\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Prerequisites</h2>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-c87d2981e76e2d3b44297f7f9384b6d7\">\n<li>You need Admin or Senior Manager access to view the full team schedule</li>\n<li>Team members must be assigned to projects before they appear in the Schedule tab</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Accessing Team Schedule</h2>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-9b30407ff81b889fbe14066be0dc0891 wp-block-paragraph\">Click <strong>Team Schedule</strong> in the left sidebar.</p>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-2658a87a069879138c09eecba7a8df27 wp-block-paragraph\">The module has two tabs: <strong>Schedule</strong> and <strong>Timesheet</strong>.</p>\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Part 1 — Schedule Tab (Team Gantt View)</h2>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-6b51ce14e76d16249e86d65ef56b10bd wp-block-paragraph\">The Schedule tab shows a Gantt-style calendar of all team members’ project assignments across the company.</p>\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Reading the Gantt</h3>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-fbf85b53090dac15b7a91f81a63a61af wp-block-paragraph\">Each row represents one team member. Coloured bars across the calendar show when they are assigned to a project. The bar spans the assignment period.</p>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-ba7241f8aa7b6b7d64f5c768c383994c wp-block-paragraph\">Use this view to:</p>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-f9d9823f9235554cdd4ed90f040b908b\">\n<li>See which team members are currently deployed and where</li>\n<li>Identify gaps in deployment (unassigned periods)</li>\n<li>Spot overlapping project assignments before adding new ones</li>\n<li>Plan manpower before starting a new project phase</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Filters</h3>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color has-border-color has-palette-color-1-border-color has-fixed-layout\" style=\"border-width:2px\"><thead><tr><th>Filter</th><th>What It Does</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Project</td><td>Show only team members assigned to a specific project. Default shows all projects.</td></tr><tr><td>Date / Week</td><td>Navigate forward or backward by week to see different time periods</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Part 2 — Timesheet Tab</h2>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-08fbd040c6e426ad6fba0068fe769ea6 wp-block-paragraph\">The Timesheet tab lists all timesheet entries logged across the company.</p>\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Timesheet List Columns</h3>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color has-border-color has-palette-color-1-border-color has-fixed-layout\" style=\"border-width:2px\"><thead><tr><th>Column</th><th>What It Shows</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Name</td><td>Team member who logged the timesheet</td></tr><tr><td>Project</td><td>Project the work was logged against</td></tr><tr><td>Date</td><td>Date of the timesheet entry</td></tr><tr><td>Hours</td><td>Hours worked</td></tr><tr><td>Notes</td><td>Description of work done</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Timesheet Filters</h3>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color has-border-color has-palette-color-1-border-color has-fixed-layout\" style=\"border-width:2px\"><thead><tr><th>Filter</th><th>Options</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Project</td><td>Filter by project</td></tr><tr><td>Date</td><td>Set a date range</td></tr><tr><td>Team Member</td><td>Filter by a specific person</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Part 3 — Creating a New Timesheet Entry</h2>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-b6e0907e3a4594fac1e96f05fe530580 wp-block-paragraph\">Click <strong>+ New Timesheet</strong> in the top right of the Timesheet tab.</p>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color has-border-color has-palette-color-1-border-color has-fixed-layout\" style=\"border-width:2px\"><thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Required</th><th>What to Enter</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Team Member</strong></td><td>Yes</td><td>Select the person from the dropdown</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Project</strong></td><td>Yes</td><td>Select the project the work was done on</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Date</strong></td><td>Yes</td><td>Date the work was performed</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Hours</strong></td><td>Yes</td><td>Number of hours worked</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Notes</strong></td><td>No</td><td>Brief description of tasks completed (e.g. “Brickwork, Ground Floor, 8 hours”)</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-e96e6053b6af6cee452e36ef733b2169 wp-block-paragraph\">Click <strong>Save</strong>. The entry appears in the Timesheet list immediately.</p>\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Tips</h2>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-74cefb56f879297c59b0cdc120f19d9f\">\n<li>Use the Schedule tab before assigning someone to a new project. Check whether they already have overlapping assignments during the same period.</li>\n<li>Filter the Schedule tab by project to see the full deployed team for a specific project at a glance.</li>\n<li>Log timesheet entries same-day. Entries entered days later are harder to verify against attendance records and may be disputed.</li>\n<li>Timesheet entries feed into project cost reporting. Always log against the correct project to keep project-level cost data accurate.</li>\n<li>Use the Notes field in timesheets to record what was done. Vague entries (“site work”) make cost analysis less useful than specific ones (“Plastering — Floors 2 and 3”).</li>\n</ul>\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">If Something Goes Wrong</h2>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color has-border-color has-palette-color-1-border-color has-fixed-layout\" style=\"border-width:2px\"><thead><tr><th>Problem</th><th>Likely Cause</th><th>What to Do</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Team member not appearing in Schedule tab</td><td>Not assigned to any project</td><td>Add them to a project via Settings, then Roles and Access</td></tr><tr><td>Timesheet entry missing from the list</td><td>Date filter is restricting the view</td><td>Reset the date filter to a wider range</td></tr><tr><td>Cannot save timesheet — validation error</td><td>Required field left blank</td><td>Fill in Team Member, Project, Date, and Hours before saving</td></tr><tr><td>Cannot see another team member’s schedule</td><td>Role does not have full team visibility</td><td>Ask Admin to check your role permissions</td></tr><tr><td>Gantt bar not showing for a team member</td><td>Assignment dates not set or member just added</td><td>Check project assignment dates and reload the Schedule tab</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n"
}